olive oil
1 potato
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 packet Diced Chicken
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 tsp soy sauce
1 stalk celery
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 tsp sesame oil
vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 bag parsley

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place peeled pumpkin pieces and potato on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the veggies have 10 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add sweet chilli sauce and the soy sauce, turning chicken to coat.

TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery.
• In a medium bowl, combine slaw mix, celery, mayonnaise, the sesame oil and a drizzle of vinegar. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Help toss the slaw.

• Divide sweet chilli-glazed chicken, celery slaw and roast veggie chunks between plates.
• Tear over parsley leaves to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Help tear over the parsley.